  "name": "Horrid Wilting",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "source": {
      "book": "Materia"
    },
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You draw the moisture from every creature in a 30-foot cube centered on a point you choose within range. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw. Constructs and undead are not affected, and plants, water elementals and creatures that breathe water make this saving throw with disadvantage. A creature takes [[/r 12d12]] necrotic damage on a failed save and are weakened for up to 1 minute, or half as much damage and are weakened until the end of their next turn on a successful one.</p><p>Nonmagical plants in the area that are not creatures, such as trees and shrubs, wither and die instantly.</p><p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 9th level or higher, it can be cast as a Bonus Action instead of an Action.</p>",
